Title: [5G18A][QT][Airphone]BB2 CCS service crashed during the ue attach process， RRC Connection Reconfiguration timeout
Description:
*** DEFAULT TEMPLATE for 2G-3G-4G-5G-SRAN-FDD-TDD-DCM-Micro-Controller common template v1.1.0 (09.05.2018) – PLEASE FILL IT IN BEFORE CREATING A PR AND DO NOT CHANGE / REMOVE ANY SECTION OF THIS TEMPLATE ***

[1. Detail Test Steps:]
1)AP build 4.900012.663 upgraded success. the AP BB1 and BB2 is green on the web ui.
2)Do ue attach which contains following steps:
a) start edaemon process on the AP BB2
b) start l3 process on the AP BB2
c) start ap egate process on the epc
d) In the ap egate, load basic.lua and send ue attach command

[2. Expected Result:]
1) ue attach success
2) the ccs service is ok
[3. Actual Result:]
1) the ccs service is crashed
2) ue attach failed
[4. Tester analysis:]
In uecp-0_sysinfo:
there is a timeout event after the ue attach flow msg "Sending RRC Connection Reconfiguration"
Jun 07 17:22:23 dxtl3-1-uecp-0 cplane_ue[1903]: [17:22:23.874751][1903][1903][debug] (eNB UE ID: 1PoolId: 8 MME UE ID: 50000) Sending RRC Connection Reconfiguration
Jun 07 17:22:23 dxtl3-1-uecp-0 cplane_ue[1903]: [17:22:23.875303][1903][1903][debug] UeContextSetup (without radio capabilities) - (eNB UE ID: 1PoolId: 8 MME UE ID: 50000): entering WaitForRRCConnectReconfComplete state
Jun 07 17:22:25 dxtl3-1-uecp-0 cplane_ue[1903]: [17:22:25.874792][1903][1903][debug] Timeout event received
Jun 07 17:22:25 dxtl3-1-uecp-0 cplane_ue[1903]: [17:22:25.874808][1903][1903][debug] QueuedTimerService: Timer (id=9) elapsed
Jun 07 17:22:25 dxtl3-1-uecp-0 cplane_ue[1903]: [17:22:25.874820][1903][1903][debug] Response of type messages::RRC::RRCConnectionReconfigurationComplete has not been received in time
Jun 07 17:22:25 dxtl3-1-uecp-0 cplane_ue[1903]: [17:22:25.874828][1903][1903][debug] UeContextSetup (without radio capabilities): leaving Working state
Jun 07 17:22:25 dxtl3-1-uecp-0 cplane_ue[1903]: [17:22:25.874841][1903][1903][warning] (eNB UE ID: 1PoolId: 8 MME UE ID: 50000) Initial Context Setup failed

From the log above, the ue attach failed as Response of type messages::RRC::RRCConnectionReconfigurationComplete has not been received in time which is caused by timeout event

The msg flow of ue attach is
UE-L2 send  RRC Connection Reconfiguration to UE-L3
UE-L3 send  RRCConnectionReconfigurationComplete to UE-L2.

So, there shoud be something wrong when the UE-L3 response to the UE-L2.

I doubt the CCS crashed may caused the  timeout event.
